## REST API (FastAPI) — must end with /api/v1
#
# Shared folder tip: put machine-specific values in `.env.local` (gitignored).
# Vite loads `.env.local` over `.env` — use it on Windows for the Kali VM IP:
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.56.x:8000/api/v1
#
# Backend on Kali VM, frontend on Windows:
#   1. VM IP: `ip a` on Kali; ping from Windows.
#   2. Kali: `uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --reload`
#   3. Backend `CORS_ORIGINS` must include your Vite origin (port 8080 by default).
#
# Same machine:
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000/api/v1
#
# Google Cloud / production static build (HTTPS → WebSockets use wss:// automatically):
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-api-host.example.com/api/v1
#   See deploy/gcp/README.md and deploy/gcp/firebase.json.example
#
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.56.102:8000/api/v1